By Olawale Ayeni, The National President of POHAN, the parent umbrella organisation for serving and former Public Office Holders Association of Nigeria (POHAN), Bashorun MD Eseyin, yesterday paid a courtesy visit to His Royal Majesty, Oba Dele Owoniyi, The Oba Otitoleke Oweyomade 1, Obaro of Kabba and the Chairman Okun Area traditional Council Kogi State. Chief Eseyin who made the visit to the highly respected monarch in his palace with his entourage, says it was very important and necessary for such a visit because charity begins at home. The POHAN president who in his remark praised his royal majesty for maintaining peace and orderliness under his watch, he said his reign has brought blessing and peace to Okun land, he also brief the Oba on the Objectives and visions of POHAN and further call support and partnership with the association been the umbrella body for all public office holder in the country which by extension the Oba is part of. Eseyin went ahead to present the prestigious POHAN’s seal symbol to the kabiesi. In his response the Oba thanked the national president and his entourage for a thoughtful visit, he acknowledged the formation and organization of an association as POHAN as timely and commendable. He made several royal blessings and assured the association of his support at all times. 